14 g. To an employee or agent of the division of juvenile services or the department of
15 health and human services, if necessary in the performance of the employee's or
16 agent's duty.
17 3. If the court orders a report to be open for the purpose of de-identified statistical
18 analysis, data gathering, or scientific study, the report must remain confidential.
19 4. Any incriminating statement made by a minor to the tier 1a mental health professiona l
20 as part of a fitness to proceed examination may not be used against the minor over
21 objection in any proceeding.
22 27 - 20.5 - 06. Fitness to proceed examination .
23 1. If there is reason to doubt the minor's fitness to proceed, the court shall order the
24 minor to be examined by a tier 1a mental health professional .
25 2. This section does not prohibit any party from retaining the party's own qualified tier 1a
26 mental health professional to conduct additional evaluations at the party's own
27 expense.
28 3. The fitness to proceed examination must be conducted in the least restrictive
29 environment.
