6 (2) Medical, educational, and court records reviewed; and
7 (3) Social, clinical, developmental, and available legal history.
8 b. A clinical assessment that includes:
9 (1) A mental status examination;
10 (2) The diagnosis and functional impact of mental illness, developmental
11 disability, or cognitive impairment. If the minor is taking medication, the
